A FORMER Police reservist and two other suspects were nabbed for impersonating cops in Soshanguve. This was after police received a complaint of common robbery and acted swiftly. Police conducted a search for the suspects. A vehicle that matched the description given was spotted and stopped in Soshanguve, north of Tshwane. “Upon questioning the occupants, it was established that one female is a former police reservist in Tshwane,” police spokesman Captain Mavela Masondo said in a statement. He said inside the vehicle there was police uniform, unwritten police docket, trays of eggs and livestock of chickens. “The suspects were charged with impersonating police officers, possession of suspected stolen property and common robbery. More charges might be added.” “The investigation is underway to establish how the former reservist still possessed police uniform.” The suspects are expected to appear in court soon.  